The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in session-based next item recommendation, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the use of image-like representations of item sequences, which suggests the relevance of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text embedding, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) tasks such as recommendation, which suggests the relevance of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
